  <HeroText textOnly>
    <Fragment slot='title'>
      <span class='text-[#8B3324] uppercase tracking-[0.4rem] font-special text-3xl md:text4xl'
        >What is Occupational Therapy?
      </span>
    </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot='content'>
      <div class='text-left max-w-3xl m-auto'>
        <p class='text-left'>
          Occupational Therapy (OT) is the art and science that helps individuals find meaning and purpose in their
          everyday activities. <br />Occupation' is defined as the activities that an individual, needs, wants and/or is
          expected to do. <br />A holistic, evidence-based approach is used to problem-solve areas the individual is
          having difficulty with - i.e. self-care, productivity, and leisure. OT seeks to find the 'Just Right
          Challenge' - a combination of personal and environmental factors, as well as the activity demands so the
          individual can achieve full participation and engagement in their chosen occupations.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Fragment>
  </HeroText>

  <!-- Content Widget **************** -->

